                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A marble funerary plaque, broken into multiple fragments and currently reconnected with plaster filling the voids. Orsi records 7 fragments (in both the Taccuini and the NSA), although the inventory entries both note only 6 fragments, and the transcription under inv.50779 (1948) misses the final letters lower right of the 7th fragment. The 7th fragment was not with the stone when last inspected (2015). It is unclear from Orsi's drawing whether the lower left corner was fully preserved in the 7th fragment originally or not, and therefore as it is currently preserved, at least one line is lost at the bottom. The plaque is thicker at the top than at the bottom.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/257.html">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">39</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">23.7</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">1.8-2.5</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.fragments.contiguous"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Well-spaced lines filling the width of the available stone, word-breaks do not observe line-end.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.incomplete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
