                    <lb n="9"/><num atLeast="33" atMost="53"><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">X</supplied><gap reason="lost" unit="character" atLeast="1" atMost="2"/><unclear>X</unclear>XIII</num> <space unit="character" quantity="1"/>
                    <lb n="10"/><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor"><orig>SFV</orig></supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                 </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="line 6"><note>The top of the B is visible above the break. The final two Es on this line appear either partially or entirely to lack the lowermost stroke.</note></app>
                 </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>To the shades of the departed. This memorial of Cesernius Marcelus his wife and sons set up for a well deserving man, who lived 43 (?) years ...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The fragment recorded by Orsi from the lower left recorded an initial X to the numeral and three letters in a 10th line below, which are not easily resolved in a common abbreviation but likely to pertain to the erection of the memorial by Cesernius Marcelus' family. The position of the X at the start of line 9, with at least a partial vacat of one character implied before it in the drawing by Orsi leaves it slightly uncertain exactly what the total age in years recorded was, with a minimum of 33 and a maximum of 53, but 43 seeming the most likely from the spacing on the fragments preserved. The repetition of X across line-break in both uxor and vixit is notable.</p>
            </div>
